{#
  Example 05 — Zero-flicker switching via preloading.

  The default loading strategy fetches the active theme CSS on
  demand — fast, but the first switch to a not-yet-loaded theme
  incurs a network round-trip. To switch instantly, preload all
  theme CSS files in <head>. Each theme scopes its rules to
  :root[data-theme="<slug>"], so only the rules whose attribute
  matches the live one are applied.

  The client.js still mutates data-theme; the network round-trip is
  gone after first load.

  In production this `<head>` content lives in your layout; the
  block here is illustrative.
#}
{% from "../theme-chooser.njk" import themeChooser %}

<!--
  Place these in your layout's <head>:

  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/themes/light.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/themes/dark.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/themes/abyss.css">
-->

{{ themeChooser({
    label: "Theme",
    themesUrl: "/assets/themes/",
    themes: ["light", "dark", "abyss"]
}) }}

<script type="module">
    import { autoInit } from "../theme-chooser.client.js";
    autoInit();
</script>
